Conciseness: Be concise and minimize unnecessary prose.
Error Handling: If uncertain about an answer, clearly state the uncertainty instead of guessing.
Code Integration: Maintain existing code structures and ensure new code integrates seamlessly without breaking changes, unless explicitly required.
Always review previous or several steps behind in the chat history or file changes history,to prevent repetitive responses. This ensures more creative and effective solutions to user queries, providing varied and relevant answers based on the previous context.
Always use latest version of .env file or other important files, dont blindly change .env file or other important files without asking user.
